response.Q0:
i first viewed the last 3 nodes and went to the direction if the highest amount.
if all 3 were very low, on the minus side, then i either took a risk to go to an unexplored route or to go to the one with lesser loss.
response.Q1:
yes. at first i revealed the nodes of my first step which would still end in loss if i landed at a very low number.

i changed to revealing the further nodes and in yielded better results.
response.Q2: it was neither difficult nor easy considering that it was very unpredictable and even with the opportunity to see some of the nodes prices before staring, what the nodes on the path yielded was unknown and other times knowing the last 3 was of no help if all 3 were of very low amounts which would most probably results in a negative amount.
i was fun to play the game. it was a bit challenging at first but after a few rounds it became enjoyable and very engaging, considering that i had to be fast and pay attention.
